Decl

Decl is a semantically oriented declarative language that uses
Perl as its "assembler".  Its development process is currently
undergoing a reboot after an extended period of neglect. (I
realized I could do better than the first try.)

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Decl

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Decl

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Decl

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Decl

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Decl/


